We'd like you to meet <b>Kevin</b>, our Featured Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Kevin has been maxing and relaxing in Millsberry since November 28th, 2008&mdash;settling, not long after his arrival, into the popular Lakeview neighborhood. <br><br><a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=serpentydude"><a href='/home/?user=serpentydude'>55469-D Pond Road</a></a> is where Kevin calls home: not too far from the lake, so he'll have a fair chance of spotting the ever-elusive Sylvie.  <br><br>Kevin enjoys sailing, drawing, and foreign languages. Talk about a Renaissance man! The foreign language skills should come in handy when sailing to far-off countries.<br><br>Comical is a word often used to describe Kevin, so don't be surprised if he's got you slapping your knee with one of his signature jokes. He's also quite athletic, which should explain his trophy for Home Run Derby.<br><br>And, when Kevin's not on the sports field, he's probably saving a galaxy or two since he has a trophy for Galactic Defender, as well. He's also a master of Sudoku, so keeping his mind sharp is as important to him as protecting planets. <br><br>If you're thinking of buying a CD for Kevin, his favorite tunes are rap, classical, and modern rock. There's quite a variety there, so you really can't go wrong. <br><br>Next time you see Kevin, be sure to congratulate him and thank him for being such an amazing citizen!<br></div>
